Irish Foliage ‚òòÔ∏è üå≤ autumn üçÇ  with Hasselblad Views
.
Ireland is one of the warmest European countries. So its makes for warmer autumn walks, with a little more sun coming through onto the cascading colourful leaves.
.
This tree had many different colours of leaves. Green climbers coming up the trunk, and was shuffled in amongst other autumn trees changing to rich red colours. 
Its almost impossible to recapture the real life experience - but the Hasselblad does a pretty excellent job. You can even see the blues coming in through the tops of the trees. .
Truly beautiful. .
.
.
.

Getting up before the crack of dawn to drive a PORSCHE 911 on the old Military Road in the haunted Scottish highlands.
.
These clear skied mornings are about 1 degrees Celsius.
.
No traffic, no police, sports exhaust and technicolor leaves. .
I don‚Äôt get the same thrills driving and photographing that I used to. Doing these things used to give me such a kick because I felt I was proving something to myself. .
I found it hard to understand where the thrill had gone.
.
Then I realised I‚Äôd shifted to a wholesome feeling of satisfaction. A personal happiness, driving cars and taking photos. .
Rather than a social high of proving new things to myself. .
Thanks to my LEGENDARY Scottish mate for loaning the Porsche. 
And thanks for autumn Scotland for always delivering.
.
And Hasselblad. .
.
.
.
.
